This directory is required to exist by examples/tcps-generated/ggen.toml's
[templates].dir = "templates" config, but this example sources all its actual
templates from its [[packs]] entries (tcps-core-pack, tcps-std-pack, etc.), not
from local files here. Git does not track empty directories, so on a fresh
checkout (e.g. CI) this directory was silently absent, causing `ggen sync run`
to fail with FM-CONFIG-004 (templates dir unreadable) before it ever got a
chance to read the packs. This .gitkeep exists solely to keep the directory
present after `git clone`.
